This paper deals with natural language generation and data maintenance, which are common topics in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of knowledge bases and the need to mine information from them suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The evaluation of the system's performance and comparison to other approaches involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
